00:11:51,767 --> 00:11:54,031
Wow, what good weather!

186
00:11:54,031 --> 00:11:55,398
Secretary Hwang. Long time no see.

187
00:11:55,398 --> 00:11:56,433
Hello.

188
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,400
What brings you here?

189
00:11:57,401 --> 00:12:00,266
The CEO said he'll drive himself to cover the story.

190
00:12:00,266 --> 00:12:02,498
I know. I just have something to give him.

191
00:12:02,498 --> 00:12:04,332
Oh? What is it?

192
00:12:04,332 --> 00:12:07,998
What's this? Damyung Construction?

193
00:12:07,998 --> 00:12:09,633
It's a company CEO Yoo invested in.

194
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:12,067
They sent a gift to celebrate the contract.

195
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:15,131
Lucky him. He can invest so easily.

196
00:12:15,131 --> 00:12:16,899
And receive gifts so easily.

197
00:12:16,899 --> 00:12:18,198
It wasn't easy.

198
00:12:18,198 --> 00:12:20,199
It almost fell through. He worked hard for this.

199
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:23,220
- Then goodbye. 
 - Bye.

200
00:12:28,466 --> 00:12:30,264
So that's why he came here on the weekend

201
00:12:30,265 --> 00:12:32,865
and moved his desk and cleaned the place.

202
00:12:32,865 --> 00:12:35,580
To put the investment out of his mind.

203
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:40,460

204
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:43,666
This is my house. Isn't it perfect?

205
00:12:43,666 --> 00:12:45,898
A rooftop party in the city.

206
00:12:45,898 --> 00:12:46,964
Yes.

207
00:12:46,964 --> 00:12:50,099
Enjoying the city nightscape in the open space,

208
00:12:50,099 --> 00:12:53,433
having a barbeque party and drinking cold beer.

209
00:12:53,433 --> 00:12:57,699
A rooftop house is a dream for youth on their own.

210
00:12:57,699 --> 00:12:59,399
That is nonsense.

211
00:12:59,399 --> 00:13:01,431
I want to run away from her as soon as possible.

212
00:13:01,432 --> 00:13:02,465
What?

213
00:13:02,465 --> 00:13:06,532
That kind of dream is an illusion made in TV shows and movies.

214
00:13:06,532 --> 00:13:08,331
It's hot in the summer and cold in the winter.

215
00:13:08,331 --> 00:13:09,600
It's infested with bugs.

216
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,032
And when it rains—

217
00:13:11,033 --> 00:13:13,267
it floods and becomes a water park.

218
00:13:13,267 --> 00:13:15,498
Oh? How did you know?

219
00:13:15,498 --> 00:13:17,331
I lived in a rooftop house, too.

220
00:13:17,331 --> 00:13:18,931
I see.

221
00:13:18,931 --> 00:13:22,566
Want some tips so you can live here a little less uncomfortably?

222
00:13:22,566 --> 00:13:26,366
 Put a bubble wrap on the front door and put the furniture against the outer wall.

223
00:13:26,366 --> 00:13:28,999
 It will help to retain heat.

224
00:13:28,999 --> 00:13:31,799
 Put up black-out curtains to prevent

225
00:13:31,799 --> 00:13:34,199
 furniture and clothes from losing color.

226
00:13:34,199 --> 00:13:36,866
 And if you clean the drain in advance

227
00:13:36,866 --> 00:13:39,799
 it won't become a water park when it rains.

228
00:13:39,799 --> 00:13:43,167
 Oh! You must install a filter.

229
00:13:44,165 --> 00:13:45,865
They're great tips.

230
00:13:45,865 --> 00:13:50,500
It's know-how from a person who experienced it.

231
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,733
When will my apartment get reconstructed

232
00:13:58,734 --> 00:14:01,966
and become a new apartment like that?

233
00:14:03,033 --> 00:14:06,966
Do you know my apartment's reconstruction is on hold?

234
00:14:06,966 --> 00:14:09,199
There's so little chance

235
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,598
that even the resident representative moved.

236
00:14:11,599 --> 00:14:12,965
Really?

237
00:14:12,966 --> 00:14:15,165
Shocking, right?

238
00:14:15,165 --> 00:14:19,431
What's more shocking is that no one wanted to take the job.

239
00:14:19,431 --> 00:14:22,232
What's even more shocking

240
00:14:22,232 --> 00:14:25,164
is that my wife ended up taking the job.

241
00:14:25,164 --> 00:14:26,266
Really?

242
00:14:26,266 --> 00:14:27,800
Yes!

243
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:30,298
But what's even more shocking

244
00:14:30,299 --> 00:14:32,431
is that since she is the resident representative,

245
00:14:32,432 --> 00:14:34,932
she'll push ahead like a bulldozer.

246
00:14:34,932 --> 00:14:39,565
So there's still hope for reconstruction.

247
00:14:42,099 --> 00:14:43,766
There's another shocking news.

248
00:14:43,766 --> 00:14:44,599
What?

249
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:48,500
The home owner's appendix burst and went to the ER.

250
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:50,599
Today's cover is a bust.

251
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:53,534
We should head back to the office.

252
00:14:53,534 --> 00:14:58,733
Since we're already out, let's go get some fresh air.

253
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,380
Sir?

254
00:15:16,567 --> 00:15:18,900
It must be around here.

255
00:15:21,432 --> 00:15:22,465
You're here.

256
00:15:22,466 --> 00:15:23,367
Hi!

257
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:26,090
Come on in.

258
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:32,830

259
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:37,164
You decorated the place so well.

260
00:15:37,164 --> 00:15:38,331
Thank you.

261
00:15:38,331 --> 00:15:39,966
Cleaning is my hobby.

262
00:15:39,966 --> 00:15:42,033
I see.

263
00:15:42,033 --> 00:15:44,465
But don't you get mold even though you clean often?

264
00:15:44,465 --> 00:15:45,699
How did you know?

265
00:15:45,699 --> 00:15:48,199
I lived in many semi-basements.

266
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:51,131
It's a war against dampness when you live in one.

267
00:15:51,131 --> 00:15:55,832
If you put charcoal in the wardrobe...

268
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:59,600
You already did it.

269
00:16:00,766 --> 00:16:02,232
Oh, and...

270
00:16:02,232 --> 00:16:05,366
It gets damp between clothes in the drawer.

271
00:16:05,366 --> 00:16:06,798
If you put newspapers...

272
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:09,832
You already did.

273
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:11,064
Well...

274
00:16:11,065 --> 00:16:13,532
If you don't like people seeing in from outside,

275
00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:15,399
- put a foggy sheet— 
 - So they can't see in from outside.

276
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:16,033
What?

277
00:16:16,034 --> 00:16:18,498
I pasted a screening sheet on the windows.

278
00:16:18,498 --> 00:16:22,533
You can see outside, but you can't see inside.

279
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,933
I didn't know about that.

280
00:16:24,934 --> 00:16:29,000
You really know how to live in a semi-basement.

281
00:16:29,667 --> 00:16:32,266
I'll drive the kids this weekend.

282
00:16:32,266 --> 00:16:35,832
You do your best as the resident representative.

283
00:16:35,832 --> 00:16:38,232
Okay. Bye.

284
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:42,067
I can't even get some rest this weekend.

285
00:16:43,099 --> 00:16:46,799
Why do you live hard, Chief Editor?

286
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:51,598
Of course, to feed my wife and kids.

287
00:16:51,598 --> 00:16:56,367
I don't have anyone to feed. Why am I living hard?

288
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,766
What do you mean?

289
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:05,699
What's my purpose in toiling away and earning money?

290
00:17:05,699 --> 00:17:09,000
I don't know and I feel empty.

291
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:10,365
You feel empty?

292
00:17:10,366 --> 00:17:12,232
You're a success.

293
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:15,034
If I were you,

294
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:19,200
I'd think life was so fun and exciting.

295
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,732
Why?

296
00:17:20,732 --> 00:17:23,065
Just as you said,

297
00:17:23,066 --> 00:17:26,632
you don't have a family to take care of.

298
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:28,599
You have more than enough money.

299
00:17:28,599 --> 00:17:31,998
You can use all that on yourself to enjoy life.

300
00:17:31,998 --> 00:17:38,400
If I were you, I'd go crazy.

301
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:01,633
How much does all this cost?

302
00:18:01,633 --> 00:18:04,266
It's so good.

303
00:18:04,266 --> 00:18:07,365
I'm enjoying this luxury thanks to you.

304
00:18:07,366 --> 00:18:09,499
Have as much as you want.

305
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,566
What do you think?

306
00:18:10,566 --> 00:18:14,665
Eating good food at a high-end restaurant releases endorphins, right?

307
00:18:14,665 --> 00:18:19,390
You think life is good, that life is fun, right?

308
00:18:23,066 --> 00:18:25,167
Why are you already...

309
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:28,900
Are you already done?

310
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,470
Yes.

311
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:31,690
I guess...

312
00:18:31,690 --> 00:18:37,160
I'm not the type to feel joy eating expensive food like this.

313
00:18:42,699 --> 00:18:44,300
I'm sorry, sir.

314
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,899
You wasted money on this because of me.

315
00:18:46,899 --> 00:18:47,932
It's okay.

316
00:18:47,932 --> 00:18:50,199
At least you enjoy the food.

317
00:18:50,199 --> 00:18:52,460
Please keep eating.

318
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:03,765
Don't be so disappointed, sir.

319
00:19:03,765 --> 00:19:06,365
Fun in life isn't just in food.

320
00:19:06,365 --> 00:19:12,267
If I were you, I'd really go crazy.

321
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:15,632
What's that?

322
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:16,832
Did a partner company send it?

323
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:17,966
No.

324
00:19:17,967 --> 00:19:20,032
It's mine. I bought it.

325
00:19:20,032 --> 00:19:22,999
I set the shipping address to the office by mistake.

326
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,499
What did you buy?

327
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:25,265
Okay.

328
00:19:25,266 --> 00:19:28,366
Unboxing! It's showtime!

329
00:19:30,900 --> 00:19:33,133
Tada!

330
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:35,266
Wow, it's so pretty!

331
00:19:35,266 --> 00:19:37,499
Isn't it the same as what you're wearing?

332
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,665
Open your eyes.

333
00:19:38,666 --> 00:19:40,264
How are they the same?

334
00:19:40,265 --> 00:19:41,431
This is brown.

335
00:19:41,432 --> 00:19:42,865
This is dark brown.

336
00:19:42,866 --> 00:19:44,499
They're totally different.

337
00:19:44,499 --> 00:19:46,431
 What's so different?

338
00:19:46,432 --> 00:19:47,632
 They're the same.

339
00:19:47,633 --> 00:19:50,900
But this one's the bomb.

340
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:53,332
Ta-da!

341
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:56,766
Isn't that exactly the same?

342
00:19:56,766 --> 00:19:58,898
I don't believe your sense of fashion.

343
00:19:58,898 --> 00:20:00,998
This is one size bigger.

344
00:20:00,998 --> 00:20:02,133
This is slim fit.

345
00:20:02,133 --> 00:20:03,765
This is over fit.

346
00:20:03,765 --> 00:20:05,232
They're completely different.

347
00:20:05,233 --> 00:20:06,998
 How are they different?

348
00:20:06,998 --> 00:20:09,366
 She's so wasteful.

349
00:20:09,366 --> 00:20:11,400
What's this?

350
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:13,898
How is that different?

351
00:20:13,898 --> 00:20:15,431
- It's the same. 
 - What?

352
00:20:15,431 --> 00:20:17,164
I guess I forgot and bought the same thing.

353
00:20:17,164 --> 00:20:20,366
I was out of it because I was so drunk.

354
00:20:21,533 --> 00:20:24,765
 My heart pounded for that hopeless spender?

355
00:20:24,765 --> 00:20:25,999
You need to get a refund.

356
00:20:25,999 --> 00:20:27,164
I can't be bothered.

357
00:20:27,164 --> 00:20:27,900
You wear it.

358
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:29,600
Really?

359
00:20:31,532 --> 00:20:32,366
Thank you.

360
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:35,266
 My heart must've malfunctioned for a moment.

361
00:20:35,266 --> 00:20:38,565
 What a waste of my heartbeat!

362
00:20:38,565 --> 00:20:40,565
What do you think, Editor Nam?

363
00:20:40,565 --> 00:20:43,033
Hey, Editor Nam!

364
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:43,666
What?

365
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:45,232
Why are you so spaced out?

366
00:20:45,232 --> 00:20:46,732
I was?

367
00:20:46,732 --> 00:20:48,800
No way.

368
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:55,866
What's up with him?

369
00:20:55,866 --> 00:20:58,732
Why in the world is he so dazed?

370
00:20:58,732 --> 00:21:00,866
Perhaps...

371
00:21:00,866 --> 00:21:03,932
Because of this?

372
00:21:06,432 --> 00:21:08,199
What's this?

373
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:21,865
Wow, you look like a Kingsman.

374
00:21:21,866 --> 00:21:23,332
I'm surprised, too.

375
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:26,865
Like you said, seeing this transformation,

376
00:21:26,866 --> 00:21:29,598
I feel life is worth living.

377
00:21:29,599 --> 00:21:33,266
I guess I'm the type of person that feels joy in dressing up and showing off.

378
00:21:33,266 --> 00:21:35,065
See? What did I tell you...

379
00:21:35,066 --> 00:21:37,633
Is what I should say.

380
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:40,632
I should be happy, for your sake.

381
00:21:42,367 --> 00:21:47,665
But I guess I'm not the type to feel joy wearing expensive clothes to show off.

382
00:21:47,666 --> 00:21:49,900
Oh, is that so?

383
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:55,500
If I were you, I'd be so excited.

384
00:21:55,500 --> 00:21:59,898
I guess it was my own dream again this time.

385
00:21:59,898 --> 00:22:02,999
Well, then, why don't you try one on?

386
00:22:02,999 --> 00:22:04,665
What?

387
00:22:04,666 --> 00:22:07,532
Oh, oh, oh, no, sir.

388
00:22:08,599 --> 00:22:14,699
Well, without you, I'd never visit a place like this.

389
00:22:14,699 --> 00:22:19,565
Then since I'm here, I'll just calmly try one on.

390
00:22:19,565 --> 00:22:21,234
Just for fun.

391
00:22:35,332 --> 00:22:38,865
The premium fabric fits my body like a glove.

392
00:22:38,866 --> 00:22:40,732
Expensive clothes are really different.

393
00:22:40,732 --> 00:22:42,600
Is that so?

394
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:44,266
Excuse me!

395
00:22:46,734 --> 00:22:50,599
Please proceed with the bill for the suit he is wearing now and the ones he tried out.

396
00:22:50,599 --> 00:22:51,765
What?

397
00:22:51,765 --> 00:22:53,965
Oh, no, sir. It's okay.

398
00:22:53,965 --> 00:22:56,331
I was just trying them on for fun.

399
00:22:56,331 --> 00:22:59,133
Just take it. It's a gift.

400
00:22:59,133 --> 00:23:00,566
Why all of a sudden...

401
00:23:00,566 --> 00:23:02,198
You never know.

402
00:23:02,199 --> 00:23:05,965
As I become more generous, I might feel joy in such acts.

403
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:07,467
What?

404
00:23:25,699 --> 00:23:28,700
Umm... Sir...

405
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:31,467
Why Jejudo Island all of a sudden...

406
00:23:31,467 --> 00:23:34,332
And first class at that...

407
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:39,031
You said if you were me, you'd go on a day trip to see Jejudo's emerald sea via first class.

408
00:23:39,032 --> 00:23:41,100
Enjoy it.

409
00:23:42,467 --> 00:23:44,866
Why are you doing this for me...?

410
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:49,332
Seeing you so happy, I think it makes me happy, too.

411
00:23:49,332 --> 00:23:50,565
Sir?

412
00:23:50,565 --> 00:23:55,832
I guess I'm the type that feels joy in being generous.

413
00:23:55,832 --> 00:23:58,466
Oh, I see.

414
00:23:58,500 --> 00:24:01,466
Then that's a relief.

415
00:24:18,734 --> 00:24:20,400
Editor Na.

416
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:26,266
Editor Na!

417
00:24:26,266 --> 00:24:27,698
What?

418
00:24:27,699 --> 00:24:29,733
Oh, Photographer Shin!

419
00:24:29,734 --> 00:24:31,733
I was organizing the interview recording.

420
00:24:31,734 --> 00:24:33,632
Aren't you working too hard?

421
00:24:33,632 --> 00:24:35,165
Not at all.

422
00:24:35,166 --> 00:24:38,232
It's something I want to write so it's not hard.

423
00:24:38,233 --> 00:24:40,365
You haven't had dinner yet, right?

424
00:24:40,366 --> 00:24:43,599
- Let's go eat. 
 - What?

425
00:24:43,599 --> 00:24:47,866
You said we couldn't be convenience store mates because you're preparing to study fine art.

426
00:24:47,866 --> 00:24:51,099
Today, let's go somewhere else instead of there.

427
00:24:51,099 --> 00:24:52,866
Where?

428
00:24:53,800 --> 00:24:56,366
I've never been to a place like this.

429
00:24:56,366 --> 00:24:57,965
Thank you.

430
00:24:57,965 --> 00:25:01,633
The food is so good and the photos are wonderful.

431
00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:03,832
I'm glad you like it.

432
00:25:03,832 --> 00:25:06,733
Seeing the photos reminds me of something.

433
00:25:06,734 --> 00:25:10,165
People only see what they want to,

434
00:25:10,166 --> 00:25:14,799
but a photo records every single thing

435
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:17,198
it saw in the same time and place.

436
00:25:17,199 --> 00:25:20,166
I read it in an article a photographer wrote.

437
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:22,165
- That's correctly put. 
 - Right? I thought so, too.

438
00:25:22,166 --> 00:25:24,598
Right? I thought so, too.

439
00:25:24,599 --> 00:25:26,599
Especially now that I see the photos here.

440
00:25:29,699 --> 00:25:32,699
Want to go out for a walk?

441
00:25:35,699 --> 00:25:38,566
Thank you for caring for me.

442
00:25:39,265 --> 00:25:42,433
I think you're a really nice person.

443
00:25:42,433 --> 00:25:43,400
Thanks.

444
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:46,499
But you don't have to worry about me now.

445
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:47,865
What?

446
00:25:47,866 --> 00:25:49,865
I know.

447
00:25:49,866 --> 00:25:54,965
That you know about me and CEO Yoo.

448
00:25:54,965 --> 00:25:58,400
That you're trying hard to comfort me.

449
00:26:00,133 --> 00:26:05,231
But I'm really fine now, so you don't have to...

450
00:26:05,231 --> 00:26:06,966
It's not comforting.

451
00:26:06,967 --> 00:26:10,432
- I like you. 
 - What?

452
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:11,966
I'm not trying to comfort you.

453
00:26:11,967 --> 00:26:14,434
I'm doing this because I like you.

454
00:26:15,633 --> 00:26:18,967
This isn't how I wanted to confess.

455
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:24,065
Photographer Shin...

456
00:26:24,066 --> 00:26:25,299
I know.

457
00:26:25,300 --> 00:26:27,499
You're taken aback.

458
00:26:27,499 --> 00:26:34,332
But I'm not asking you to give me an answer right now.

459
00:26:34,332 --> 00:26:38,900
I just wanted you to know how I feel.

460
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:43,765
Until you're okay, until your wound heals,

461
00:26:43,765 --> 00:26:46,132
I'll wait by your side.

462
00:26:47,233 --> 00:26:50,532
I can do that, right?

463
00:27:05,265 --> 00:27:07,267
I'm home.

464
00:27:07,267 --> 00:27:10,264
The kids will be home soon. Wash up and sleep.

465
00:27:10,265 --> 00:27:13,333
I don't even get a glance?

466
00:27:19,133 --> 00:27:20,966
What's this Hallabong?

467
00:27:20,967 --> 00:27:23,765
Oh, boy. What's that suit?

468
00:27:23,765 --> 00:27:26,700
- Where did you get the money... 
 - The CEO bought this for me as a gift.

469
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:31,031
I'm respected this much at work.

470
00:27:31,032 --> 00:27:33,467
Then ask him to give you a raise.

471
00:27:36,633 --> 00:27:38,499
What are you looking at?

472
00:27:38,500 --> 00:27:42,399
Proposals of constructors bidding for the reconstruction.

473
00:27:42,399 --> 00:27:46,733
It's giving me a headache. I shouldn't have become the representative.

474
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,832
You made such a fuss to be it.

475
00:27:54,066 --> 00:27:58,040
Oh, well. Let's tidy up and go to bed.

476
00:27:58,040 --> 00:27:59,760

477
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:00,866
What?

478
00:28:00,866 --> 00:28:02,867
Damyung Construction?

479
00:28:03,833 --> 00:28:06,365
Hold on. Where did I hear that name?

480
00:28:06,366 --> 00:28:08,065
 Damyung Construction?

481
00:28:08,066 --> 00:28:09,365
 It's a company CEO Yoo invested in.

482
00:28:09,365 --> 00:28:10,333
Right!

483
00:28:10,334 --> 00:28:13,067
Oh! That's right! It's that Damyung!

484
00:28:13,067 --> 00:28:17,532
Oh! They placed a bid.

485
00:28:17,532 --> 00:28:19,067
What?

486
00:28:19,067 --> 00:28:22,031
 My wife ended up taking the job.

487
00:28:22,032 --> 00:28:23,832
 Really?

488
00:28:25,233 --> 00:28:27,499
As soon as he heard that, he suddenly...

489
00:28:27,499 --> 00:28:28,765
 Let's go get some fresh air.

490
00:28:28,766 --> 00:28:32,531
He said there's no fun in life and he enjoys being generous.

491
00:28:32,531 --> 00:28:36,966
Is this a highly advanced strategy to win the bid?

492
00:28:36,967 --> 00:28:39,332
 As long as you enjoy the food.

493
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:40,799
 Please keep eating.

494
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:44,999
 Put the suit he's wearing right now and all the suits he tried on on my account.

495
00:28:44,999 --> 00:28:48,932
 Seeing you so happy, I think it makes me happy, too.

496
00:28:48,933 --> 00:28:51,266
It was all a bribe?

497
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:55,932
CEO Yoo is such a clever scum.

498
00:28:55,933 --> 00:28:57,966
Clever scum.

499
00:28:59,340 --> 00:29:01,370

500
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:28,532
 Do you want to become convenience store mates?

501
00:29:28,532 --> 00:29:31,165
 Are you still holding off on getting a boyfriend?

502
00:29:31,166 --> 00:29:33,031
 But you never know what'll happen, right?

503
00:29:33,032 --> 00:29:35,566
 I hope you stop hurting.

504
00:29:35,567 --> 00:29:39,132
 I hope your wound is healed soon.

505
00:29:40,866 --> 00:29:42,966
 It's not comforting.

506
00:29:42,966 --> 00:29:46,266
 I like you.

507
00:30:22,734 --> 00:30:24,733
Welcome, sir.

508
00:30:24,733 --> 00:30:26,765
Good morning, sir.

509
00:30:29,766 --> 00:30:32,300
You're here.

510
00:30:32,300 --> 00:30:34,766
- What time is today's meeting? 
 - Three o'clock.

511
00:30:34,766 --> 00:30:37,767
Can we... push the meeting

512
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:40,299
to tomorrow?

513
00:30:40,300 --> 00:30:42,733
I'm very tired today.

514
00:30:42,734 --> 00:30:47,665
As you know, our schedule yesterday was packed.

515
00:30:47,665 --> 00:30:51,098
Oh, okay. Let's do it tomorrow.

516
00:30:53,666 --> 00:30:55,966
 I was right.

517
00:30:55,967 --> 00:31:00,631
Chief Editor. Why are you acting like that to the CEO?

518
00:31:00,631 --> 00:31:03,032
I'm more shocked that he's letting it slide.

519
00:31:03,032 --> 00:31:07,466
I can show you more shocking things if I want to.

520
00:31:07,466 --> 00:31:08,698
What do you mean?

521
00:31:08,699 --> 00:31:13,099
Never mind.

522
00:31:15,032 --> 00:31:18,432
Should I suck him dry?

523
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:23,566
What time should we have the meeting tomorrow?

524
00:31:23,566 --> 00:31:25,399
I don't know.

525
00:31:25,399 --> 00:31:27,433
For me...

526
00:31:28,090 --> 00:31:29,466
The morning is good.

527
00:31:29,467 --> 00:31:35,000
Can we do tomorrow's meeting the day after?

528
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:36,765
You see, I plan

529
00:31:36,765 --> 00:31:39,933
- to be tired until tomorrow. 
 - What?

530
00:31:39,933 --> 00:31:42,299
You said you enjoy being generous.

531
00:31:42,299 --> 00:31:45,099
You can be that generous.

532
00:31:45,099 --> 00:31:46,431
Oh, well. Okay, then.

533
00:31:46,431 --> 00:31:50,866
Since you're being generous, take me to a hot spring.

534
00:31:50,866 --> 00:31:52,866
So that I can relieve my fatigue.

535
00:31:52,866 --> 00:31:55,132
Okay. Yuseong Hot Springs is nearby.

536
00:31:55,132 --> 00:31:57,399
No. Not in Korea.

537
00:31:57,399 --> 00:31:58,865
Overseas. What?

538
00:31:58,865 --> 00:32:00,633
Broaden the scale.

539
00:32:00,633 --> 00:32:03,233
Well. If you want, then okay.

540
00:32:03,233 --> 00:32:05,366
Stop!

541
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:09,499
Sir. I'm very disappointed in you.

542
00:32:09,499 --> 00:32:10,866
Do you feel joy in being generous?

543
00:32:10,866 --> 00:32:13,700
- You're not seeking some other kind of joy? 
 - What?

544
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:14,865
What do you mean...?

545
00:32:14,865 --> 00:32:17,031
Damyung Construction that you invested in!

546
00:32:17,031 --> 00:32:19,633
They're bidding for my apartment reconstruction.

547
00:32:19,633 --> 00:32:22,800
That's why you bribed me.

548
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,133
But I want to tell you.

549
00:32:25,133 --> 00:32:27,498
I'm not a man to waver because of bribes.

550
00:32:27,498 --> 00:32:30,200
I don't have money! But I at least have integrity!

551
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:32,566
- Don't live like that... 
 - The investment.

552
00:32:32,566 --> 00:32:33,899
I'll pull the plug on it.

553
00:32:33,899 --> 00:32:37,099
I'll break it off with Damyung Construction.

554
00:32:37,099 --> 00:32:40,933
- What? 
 - I forgot that apartment was where you lived.

555
00:32:40,933 --> 00:32:43,965
It wasn't a bribe...?

556
00:32:43,965 --> 00:32:46,265
I can't invest when such misunderstandings exist.

557
00:32:46,265 --> 00:32:48,165
I will withdraw my investment.

558
00:32:48,165 --> 00:32:49,331
Sir?

559
00:32:49,331 --> 00:32:50,966
You don't have to go that far...

560
00:32:50,967 --> 00:32:52,931
Oh! There's another thing I must withdraw.

561
00:32:52,931 --> 00:32:55,332
The money I spent on the hotel lunch, the suits,

562
00:32:55,332 --> 00:32:56,632
and the plane ticket to Jejudo Island.

563
00:32:56,632 --> 00:32:59,467
I withdraw my intention of gifting them to you.

564
00:32:59,467 --> 00:33:01,565
Pay me back in full.

565
00:33:01,565 --> 00:33:04,300
What? Sir!

566
00:33:04,300 --> 00:33:05,665
I wasn't thinking straight.

567
00:33:05,665 --> 00:33:09,098
I thought I might live enjoying being generous,

568
00:33:09,098 --> 00:33:11,933
but that joy has gone as well.

569
00:33:11,933 --> 00:33:15,432
What joy is there to live for now?

570
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:19,700
- What's this? 
 - Her job? Content creator.

571
00:33:19,700 --> 00:33:21,866
Her age? Two years younger than you.

572
00:33:21,866 --> 00:33:23,833
- So? 
 - I'm setting you up.

573
00:33:23,833 --> 00:33:28,166
- Why all of a sudden? 
 - You need to live a new life now.

574
00:33:28,166 --> 00:33:30,100
What do you think?

575
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:33,431
She's pretty.

576
00:33:33,431 --> 00:33:34,934
- But she's not my type. 
 - What?

577
00:33:34,934 --> 00:33:36,598
I like long hair. Not short hair.

578
00:33:36,598 --> 00:33:38,832
Jeez. She can always grow it out.

579
00:33:38,832 --> 00:33:40,867
Then I'll meet her when she does.

580
00:33:40,867 --> 00:33:42,367
Darn it.

581
00:33:44,090 --> 00:33:47,432
How long? How long does it have to be?

582
00:33:47,432 --> 00:33:49,066
I'm not sure.

583
00:33:49,066 --> 00:33:51,533
As long as yours?

584
00:33:51,533 --> 00:33:53,600
Why I ought to...

585
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:57,167
As long as mine?

586
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:00,800
Florist. Same age as us.

587
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:01,832
Cute, right?

588
00:34:01,832 --> 00:34:04,631
Her hair is as long as mine.

589
00:34:04,631 --> 00:34:06,732
You're right. She's beautiful.

590
00:34:06,732 --> 00:34:08,131
Right? Then I'll call her...

591
00:34:08,131 --> 00:34:10,434
- But she's not my type. 
 - What?

592
00:34:10,434 --> 00:34:12,531
Why?

593
00:34:12,532 --> 00:34:15,965
Her hair is long, but she's short. I'll meet her when she's taller.

594
00:34:15,965 --> 00:34:17,698
What are you talking about?

595
00:34:17,698 --> 00:34:19,064
How can she grow taller at this age?

596
00:34:19,064 --> 00:34:22,566
If she drinks a lot of milk and plays basketball, who knows?

597
00:34:22,566 --> 00:34:23,965
Her growth plates might open up again.

598
00:34:23,965 --> 00:34:25,632
Why I ought to...

599
00:34:29,300 --> 00:34:31,466
How tall does she have to be?

600
00:34:31,466 --> 00:34:32,866
I'm not sure.

601
00:34:32,866 --> 00:34:35,500
- As tall as you? 
 - Jeez!

602
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:37,198
Nam Sang Soon, you're unbelievable.

603
00:34:37,198 --> 00:34:39,064
Why are you suddenly being so picky?

604
00:34:39,064 --> 00:34:41,499
Why are you so anxious to set me up?

605
00:34:41,499 --> 00:34:43,032
I told you to live a new life.

606
00:34:43,032 --> 00:34:46,366
Stop thinking useless thoughts and meet someone!

607
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:49,733
Hello? Yes.

608
00:34:49,733 --> 00:34:51,567
I'll be there.

609
00:34:53,230 --> 00:34:55,200
Seriously!

610
00:34:59,700 --> 00:35:01,899
 Useless thoughts?

611
00:35:01,899 --> 00:35:03,867
 No way.

612
00:35:03,867 --> 00:35:06,999
 Does she know my heart pounded because of her?

613
00:35:06,999 --> 00:35:11,400
 She's pushing me away to meet someone else?

614
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,100
Unbelievable.

615
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:16,000
I don't have any feelings for you now.

616
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:22,900
I found this while preparing for this month's article.

617
00:35:22,900 --> 00:35:24,432
I wanted you to know.

618
00:35:24,432 --> 00:35:26,065
Sunbaenim!

619
00:35:26,065 --> 00:35:29,299
You can apply if you have the qualifications.

620
00:35:29,299 --> 00:35:32,298
I think you do.

621
00:35:32,298 --> 00:35:34,233
Thank you.

622
00:35:34,233 --> 00:35:35,732
But...

623
00:35:35,732 --> 00:35:37,365
I already applied.

624
00:35:37,365 --> 00:35:38,766
What?

625
00:35:45,130 --> 00:35:48,232
 Study the qualifications and apply for it.

626
00:35:48,232 --> 00:35:52,432
 If there is welfare you can get, you should search aggressively and get it.

627
00:35:52,432 --> 00:35:54,931
 Oh... Thank you.

628
00:35:54,931 --> 00:35:56,698
 It's not for you.

629
00:35:56,698 --> 00:35:58,964
 It's for the company.

630
00:35:58,964 --> 00:36:01,332
 Your residence must be stable for you to work hard.

631
00:36:01,332 --> 00:36:04,799
He knew I was staying at the office.

632
00:36:04,799 --> 00:36:06,999
I guess he heard everything we said that time.

633
00:36:06,999 --> 00:36:13,065
He speaks coldly, but I think he's a really good person.

634
00:36:20,333 --> 00:36:23,166
Pharmacist. Same hair length and height as me.

635
00:36:23,166 --> 00:36:25,599
There's no one else that matches your terms.

636
00:36:25,599 --> 00:36:26,833
- So... 
 - I'll meet her.

637
00:36:26,833 --> 00:36:29,899
Really? Great!

638
00:36:29,899 --> 00:36:33,266
Hey, Yeo Ui Joo! You're not the only one that's happy.

639
00:36:33,266 --> 00:36:34,732
I'm happy, too!

640
00:36:34,733 --> 00:36:36,899
I'm meeting a girl that has the same hair length

641
00:36:36,899 --> 00:36:40,999
and height as you, but is much better than you!

642
00:36:40,999 --> 00:36:43,733
Great. So good luck.

643
00:36:43,733 --> 00:36:45,899
I'll call her right now!

644
00:36:45,899 --> 00:36:47,632
Okay!

645
00:36:50,230 --> 00:36:52,031
Now she'll know

646
00:36:52,031 --> 00:36:54,432
that I don't have feelings for her.

647
00:36:54,432 --> 00:36:57,332
How dare she think of me like that!

648
00:37:00,610 --> 00:37:02,390

649
00:37:02,390 --> 00:37:04,468
Oh, Hyungnim! Where are you going?

650
00:37:04,468 --> 00:37:06,198
I have some matters to attend to.

651
00:37:06,199 --> 00:37:07,898
Where are you guys coming from...?

652
00:37:07,898 --> 00:37:10,366
Hey! Shin Gyeom!

653
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:14,332
What's up with him?

654
00:37:14,332 --> 00:37:16,133
Keep up the good work.

655
00:37:23,390 --> 00:37:25,566
What's with this vibe?

656
00:37:35,260 --> 00:37:36,865
Hey. What's with you?

657
00:37:36,865 --> 00:37:38,767
What?

658
00:37:38,767 --> 00:37:41,199
You gave up on your crush for him.

659
00:37:41,199 --> 00:37:43,899
Why are you blowing cold now?

660
00:37:43,899 --> 00:37:47,600
Why? Are you regretting doing that now?

661
00:37:49,630 --> 00:37:50,898
Don't try to look cool.

662
00:37:50,898 --> 00:37:52,665
You're not the only one who sacrificed for love.

663
00:37:52,665 --> 00:37:53,865
Because of you, someone else...

664
00:37:53,865 --> 00:37:55,898
They broke up.

665
00:37:55,898 --> 00:37:58,566
- What? 
 - Those two...

666
00:37:58,566 --> 00:38:00,165
They broke up.

667
00:38:00,165 --> 00:38:02,532
Hyung dumped her. Without any warning.

668
00:38:02,532 --> 00:38:05,032
- Really? 
 - Yeah.

669
00:38:05,032 --> 00:38:07,699
I guess I didn't know him that well.

670
00:38:07,699 --> 00:38:12,333
I didn't think he would hurt someone like that.

671
00:38:12,333 --> 00:38:14,367
What the...

672
00:38:24,430 --> 00:38:25,531
You heard?

673
00:38:25,532 --> 00:38:27,399
Editor Nam is going on a blind date.

674
00:38:27,399 --> 00:38:28,698
Yes.

675
00:38:28,698 --> 00:38:31,932
You should go on a date as a fresh start, too.

676
00:38:31,932 --> 00:38:33,832
I know a guy from college who's really great.

677
00:38:33,832 --> 00:38:36,331
He's also a romanticist.

678
00:38:36,331 --> 00:38:39,066
You should meet a guy like him.

679
00:38:39,066 --> 00:38:41,700
Someone who only sees you.

680
00:38:43,530 --> 00:38:45,766
I should.

681
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:51,365
That would be right...

682
00:38:53,460 --> 00:38:55,967
What's wrong?

683
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,833
I wish CEO Yoo were a bad person.

684
00:39:02,266 --> 00:39:05,500
Then I'd be able to get over him more easily.

685
00:39:06,430 --> 00:39:10,299
Why does he have to be a good person?

686
00:39:10,299 --> 00:39:13,267
What are you talking about?

687
00:39:14,660 --> 00:39:17,865
Stop crying!

688
00:39:17,865 --> 00:39:19,832
Young Won...

689
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:43,365
They're the same clothes, but she says they aren't.

690
00:39:43,365 --> 00:39:46,398
So many parcels for Editor Yeo come to the office.

691
00:39:46,398 --> 00:39:48,565
She is so thoughtless. Tsk, tsk.

692
00:39:48,565 --> 00:39:50,698
The food's going cold. You should eat.

693
00:39:50,698 --> 00:39:52,465
The pasta here is good.

694
00:39:52,465 --> 00:39:54,099
Since you mentioned pasta, that reminds me.

695
00:39:54,099 --> 00:39:55,832
You know how Editor Yeo goes crazy over pasta?

696
00:39:55,832 --> 00:39:58,666
When she sees pasta, she's like...

697
00:39:58,666 --> 00:40:00,898
She sucks it in like a vacuum cleaner.

698
00:40:00,898 --> 00:40:03,432
She eats so voraciously.

699
00:40:03,432 --> 00:40:05,434
I see.

700
00:40:06,130 --> 00:40:09,499
Oh. I heard you won a subscription.

701
00:40:09,499 --> 00:40:10,865
Did Editor Yeo tell you even that?

702
00:40:10,865 --> 00:40:14,067
Oh, come on. Seriously.

703
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,599
I'm sorry.

704
00:40:17,599 --> 00:40:19,432
Since you brought that up, it reminds me.

705
00:40:19,432 --> 00:40:21,399
I was in line to apply for a subscription.

706
00:40:21,399 --> 00:40:23,532
But I suddenly had to go to the bathroom.

707
00:40:23,532 --> 00:40:25,532
So I texted Editor Yeo.

708
00:40:25,532 --> 00:40:28,100
- I promised to set her up if she... 
 - Excuse me.

709
00:40:28,100 --> 00:40:32,966
- Yes? 
 - Do you like Ui Joo?

710
00:40:34,500 --> 00:40:37,132
What... Are you...

711
00:40:38,730 --> 00:40:40,766
Editor Yeo is just a colleague!

712
00:40:40,766 --> 00:40:43,531
It seems like she's more than that.

713
00:40:43,531 --> 00:40:45,732
It looks like you already like her a lot.

714
00:40:45,732 --> 00:40:47,466
That's nonsense!

715
00:40:47,466 --> 00:40:49,531
If I did, would I be here?

716
00:40:49,531 --> 00:40:53,399
She's the type of woman that's impossible to like.

717
00:40:53,399 --> 00:40:57,233
- Don't get me wrong. 
 - I don't think I'm getting you wrong.

718
00:40:57,233 --> 00:40:58,766
Well, then.

719
00:40:58,766 --> 00:41:01,132
I'll be going now.

720
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:08,367
What is she saying?

721
00:41:08,367 --> 00:41:10,866
What nonsense.

722
00:41:18,199 --> 00:41:19,599
Are you leaving now?

723
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:21,698
Oh, yes.

724
00:41:21,699 --> 00:41:23,965
It's late. I'll drive you home.

725
00:41:23,965 --> 00:41:25,632
No, it's okay.

726
00:41:25,632 --> 00:41:27,531
It's because I want to.

727
00:41:27,532 --> 00:41:29,032
Let's go.

728
00:41:29,934 --> 00:41:31,999
Photographer Shin.

729
00:41:35,299 --> 00:41:37,465
I have something to say.

730
00:41:40,532 --> 00:41:43,000
- Photographer Shin, I— 
 - Wait.

731
00:41:44,566 --> 00:41:46,066
Those words...

732
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:49,665
- Could I not hear what it is? 
 - What?

733
00:41:49,665 --> 00:41:52,699
I think I know what you're about to say.

734
00:41:53,399 --> 00:41:57,800
But a person's heart

735
00:41:57,800 --> 00:42:01,133
might change as time goes by.

736
00:42:04,133 --> 00:42:07,400
When the storm in you ceases,

737
00:42:08,799 --> 00:42:12,633
and what you want to say hasn't changed,

738
00:42:14,866 --> 00:42:18,033
you can tell me then.

739
00:42:29,532 --> 00:42:31,132
- Welcome. 
 - Hello.

740
00:42:31,133 --> 00:42:32,533
Hello.

741
00:42:33,399 --> 00:42:36,200
Sir! Good morning.

742
00:42:36,232 --> 00:42:37,833
Chief Editor...

743
00:42:37,833 --> 00:42:39,465
Why are there so many empty seats?

744
00:42:39,465 --> 00:42:41,132
Editor Yeo is out to cover a story.

745
00:42:41,133 --> 00:42:43,531
Editor Na has gone to her home in Chuncheon.

746
00:42:43,531 --> 00:42:46,799
- She submitted a leave of absence a few days ago. 
 - Why did she go to Chuncheon?

747
00:42:46,799 --> 00:42:50,032
I don't know what's going on in my home, how should I know about hers?

748
00:42:50,032 --> 00:42:51,933
Get to work!

749
00:42:53,433 --> 00:42:55,666
Sir, I did well...

750
00:43:00,399 --> 00:43:03,900
Of course, he doesn't want to talk to me.

751
00:43:03,900 --> 00:43:06,799
He won't want to treat me like a human being.

752
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:13,898
 Why did she go to Chuncheon?

753
00:43:13,899 --> 00:43:17,133
 I hope nothing bad has happened.

754
00:43:19,065 --> 00:43:21,600
Why do you want to know?

755
00:43:21,600 --> 00:43:23,666
What right do you have?

756
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:27,466
Come in.

757
00:43:28,533 --> 00:43:30,233
What is it?

758
00:43:33,232 --> 00:43:38,732
Well... I calculated how much I have to pay back to you.

759
00:43:40,667 --> 00:43:44,598
The hotel restaurant lunch, suits,

760
00:43:44,598 --> 00:43:48,532
first class ticket... Add all that and it's...

761
00:43:48,532 --> 00:43:51,099
What about the Hallabong I bought you in Jejudo?

762
00:43:51,100 --> 00:43:54,765
What about the Omegi rice cakes you ate?

763
00:43:54,765 --> 00:43:58,932
If I add them, it's about...

764
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:02,666
5.8 million won ($5,800)...

765
00:44:02,666 --> 00:44:05,467
Stop. Let's stop this.

766
00:44:05,467 --> 00:44:08,698
Getting that money from you means nothing to me.

767
00:44:08,699 --> 00:44:10,265
Just leave and do your work.

768
00:44:10,266 --> 00:44:11,766
Really?

769
00:44:13,600 --> 00:44:14,933
Thank you, sir!

770
00:44:14,934 --> 00:44:17,565
I'm so sorry for misunderstanding you.

771
00:44:17,566 --> 00:44:20,766
Just get out before I change my mind...

772
00:44:44,266 --> 00:44:46,067
Nam Sang Soon, are you crazy?

773
00:44:46,067 --> 00:44:47,632
Yikes! You scared me.

774
00:44:47,632 --> 00:44:51,233
You scared me! I got you the girl that fits your terms perfectly.

775
00:44:51,233 --> 00:44:53,798
- But you turned her down? 
 - She said I turned her down?

776
00:44:53,798 --> 00:44:56,232
Shut it! I did all I could.

777
00:44:56,232 --> 00:44:58,064
Live alone for the rest of your life.

778
00:44:58,065 --> 00:45:01,700
Live a pitiful single life until the day you die.

779
00:45:04,399 --> 00:45:06,000
What?

780
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:09,131
I don't think I deserve such a curse.

781
00:45:09,131 --> 00:45:10,833
I understand why she's angry.

782
00:45:10,833 --> 00:45:13,599
- She did that because she was worried about you. 
 - What?

783
00:45:13,599 --> 00:45:15,531
 What's up with him?

784
00:45:15,532 --> 00:45:18,999
 Why in the world is he so dazed?

785
00:45:18,999 --> 00:45:21,100
 Perhaps...

786
00:45:23,767 --> 00:45:26,034
 What's this?

787
00:45:26,034 --> 00:45:31,733
 She was worried you'd be troubled by your ex getting married.

788
00:45:36,266 --> 00:45:37,733
 I told you to live a new life.

789
00:45:37,733 --> 00:45:40,132
 Stop thinking useless thoughts and meet someone!

790
00:45:40,133 --> 00:45:45,399
 So, she did that because she was worried about me?

791
00:45:48,366 --> 00:45:51,132
Why are you looking at this?

792
00:45:51,132 --> 00:45:54,431
You're not thinking of going to the wedding to throw a tantrum, are you?

793
00:45:54,431 --> 00:45:56,499
Don't you dare!

794
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:00,066
 That's right.

795
00:46:00,066 --> 00:46:04,032
 I should be thinking about ruining her wedding.

796
00:46:04,032 --> 00:46:07,766
 But why am I thinking only about Ui Joo?

797
00:46:07,766 --> 00:46:11,565
 Do you like Ui Joo?

798
00:46:11,566 --> 00:46:13,066
Yes.

799
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:16,167
I think I do.

800
00:46:17,065 --> 00:46:20,733
- Is something up with the CEO? 
 - What?

801
00:46:20,733 --> 00:46:23,132
He's so down these days.

802
00:46:23,133 --> 00:46:27,098
He says there's no joy in life, and that he doesn't know why he's making money.

803
00:46:27,100 --> 00:46:29,165
So he spends money recklessly.

804
00:46:29,166 --> 00:46:30,900
- He did? 
 - Yes.

805
00:46:30,900 --> 00:46:34,565
He's so drained like he's about to die tomorrow.

806
00:46:34,565 --> 00:46:37,632
You're close with the CEO.

807
00:46:37,632 --> 00:46:39,899
Do you know anything?

808
00:46:41,266 --> 00:46:42,866
No.

809
00:46:48,532 --> 00:46:51,167
Umm, Gyeom.

810
00:46:52,899 --> 00:46:59,665
Maybe Hyungnim... is suffering because he broke up with Editor Na.

811
00:46:59,665 --> 00:47:01,265
Why would he suffer?

812
00:47:01,265 --> 00:47:03,199
